---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PregnancyDueDateCalculator from '../components/PregnancyDueDateCalculator.jsx';
---

<Layout
	title="Pregnancy Due Date Calculator — Estimate Your Due Date | Clockr"
	description="Estimate your pregnancy due date from your last period, conception date, or IVF transfer date. Track weeks and days pregnant, trimester, days remaining, and progress."
	category="birthdays"
>
	<div class="pdd-page">
		<div class="pdd-header">
			<div class="pdd-eyebrow">
				<span class="pdd-eyebrow-square" aria-hidden="true"></span>
				AGE & BIRTHDAYS
			</div>
			<h1 class="pdd-title">
				<span class="pdd-gradient">Pregnancy Due Date</span><br />
				<span class="pdd-gradient">Calculator</span>
			</h1>
			<p class="pdd-subtitle">
				Estimate your due date and track your pregnancy week by week
			</p>
		</div>

		<PregnancyDueDateCalculator client:load />

		<section class="pdd-how">
			<h2 class="pdd-section-title">How it works</h2>
			<div class="pdd-how-card">
				<p>
					Most due dates are calculated using a simple guideline called
					Naegele&rsquo;s rule: add 40 weeks (280 days) to the first day of your
					last menstrual period. It&rsquo;s a helpful way to estimate timing, but
					it&rsquo;s not a prediction — bodies and babies have their own schedules,
					and your care team may refine dates based on scans and your individual
					circumstances.
				</p>
				<p>
					If you know a conception date, the estimate shifts slightly because
					pregnancy is typically dated as 38 weeks (266 days) from conception. For
					IVF, using the transfer date can be even clearer because the embryo age
					is known — this calculator uses a common estimate for a 5-day blastocyst
					transfer, but clinics may use different conventions depending on the
					transfer day and protocol.
				</p>
				<p>
					Even with the best information, a due date is best thought of as a
					landmark on the calendar, not a deadline. Only a small percentage of
					babies arrive exactly on their estimated date, and that&rsquo;s completely
					normal. Use this as a friendly guide for planning — and lean on your
					midwife or doctor for the most accurate dates and care.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="pdd-faq">
			<h2 class="pdd-section-title">Frequently asked questions</h2>
			<div class="pdd-faq-list">
				<details class="pdd-faq-item">
					<summary class="pdd-faq-question">How accurate is a due date calculator?</summary>
					<div class="pdd-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Due date calculators give a helpful estimate, but they can&rsquo;t predict
							the exact day your baby will arrive. Only around 5% of babies are born
							on their exact due date, and many arrive a little earlier or later.
							Your midwife or doctor may refine timing based on scans and your
							individual circumstances.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>

				<details class="pdd-faq-item">
					<summary class="pdd-faq-question">How is my due date calculated from my last period?</summary>
					<div class="pdd-faq-answer">
						<p>
							The most common method adds 40 weeks (280 days) to the first day of your
							last menstrual period. This is often called Naegele&rsquo;s rule. It&rsquo;s
							widely used because many people know their period date even if they
							don&rsquo;t know the exact day of conception.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>

				<details class="pdd-faq-item">
					<summary class="pdd-faq-question">What's the difference between calculating from LMP, conception, or IVF transfer?</summary>
					<div class="pdd-faq-answer">
						<p>
							LMP uses an average cycle and adds 40 weeks, while conception-based
							estimates add 38 weeks from conception. IVF transfer can be clearer
							because the embryo age is known, but clinics may use slightly different
							conventions depending on the transfer day. If you&rsquo;re unsure, use the
							date your clinic provides as your reference.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>

				<details class="pdd-faq-item">
					<summary class="pdd-faq-question">How many weeks pregnant am I?</summary>
					<div class="pdd-faq-answer">
						<p>
							This calculator shows your current pregnancy week and day (for example,
							14 weeks and 3 days). Pregnancy is usually counted from the first day of
							your last period, so if you use conception or IVF dates, the tool
							converts them into an LMP-equivalent starting point to keep the week
							count consistent.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>

				<details class="pdd-faq-item">
					<summary class="pdd-faq-question">What trimester am I in?</summary>
					<div class="pdd-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Trimester timing can vary slightly by country and clinic, but a common
							approach is: 1st trimester up to 12 weeks, 2nd trimester from 13 to 26
							weeks, and 3rd trimester from 27 weeks to birth. Your care team may
							describe these ranges a little differently, and that&rsquo;s normal.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>

				<details class="pdd-faq-item">
					<summary class="pdd-faq-question">Can my due date change as my pregnancy progresses?</summary>
					<div class="pdd-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Yes — it can. Early ultrasound measurements sometimes suggest a slightly
							different due date than an LMP-based estimate, especially if cycles are
							irregular. If your care team updates your due date, it&rsquo;s best to
							follow their guidance for appointments and planning.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>

				<details class="pdd-faq-item">
					<summary class="pdd-faq-question">When should I see a doctor or midwife to confirm my due date?</summary>
					<div class="pdd-faq-answer">
						<p>
							If you think you might be pregnant, it&rsquo;s a good idea to book in with
							a midwife or doctor as soon as you feel ready. They can confirm
							pregnancy, talk you through next steps, and arrange dating scans when
							appropriate. If you have any worrying symptoms or feel unwell, seek
							medical advice promptly.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
			</div>
		</section>

		<div class="pdd-related">
			<h3 class="pdd-related-title">Related tools</h3>
			<div class="pdd-related-grid">
				<a href="/age-calculator" class="pdd-related-card"
					><span class="pdd-related-name">Age Calculator</span></a
				>
				<a href="/days-until-birthday" class="pdd-related-card"
					><span class="pdd-related-name">Days Until Birthday</span></a
				>
				<a href="/life-in-numbers" class="pdd-related-card"
					><span class="pdd-related-name">Your Life in Numbers</span></a
				>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>

<style>
	.pdd-page {
		max-width: 800px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 60px 24px;
	}

	.pdd-header {
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: 32px;
	}

	.pdd-eyebrow {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 10px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		font-weight: 800;
		letter-spacing: 3px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.pdd-eyebrow-square {
		width: 10px;
		height: 10px;
		border-radius: 3px;
		background: #8b5cf6;
		box-shadow: 0 0 18px rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.35);
	}

	.pdd-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 64px;
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -3px;
		line-height: 1.05;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.pdd-gradient {
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.pdd-subtitle {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 16px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
		line-height: 1.6;
		margin: 0;
	}

	/* React tool styles */
	:global(.pddc-tool) {
		margin-bottom: 56px;
	}

	:global(.pddc-card) {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.2);
		border-radius: 20px;
		padding: 24px;
		box-shadow: 0 0 40px rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.06);
	}

	:global(.pddc-card-header) {
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: 18px;
	}

	:global(.pddc-card-title) {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 18px;
		font-weight: 800;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9);
		margin-bottom: 6px;
	}

	:global(.pddc-card-subtitle) {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
		line-height: 1.5;
	}

	:global(.pddc-methods) {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		gap: 10px;
		margin-bottom: 18px;
	}

	:global(.pddc-method) {
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.22);
		background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.06);
		border-radius: 14px;
		padding: 14px 14px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.75);
		cursor: pointer;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease, background 0.2s ease;
	}

	:global(.pddc-method:hover) {
		border-color: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.45);
		background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.08);
	}

	:global(.pddc-method.is-active) {
		border-color: rgba(236, 72, 153, 0.55);
		background: rgba(236, 72, 153, 0.08);
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9);
	}

	:global(.pddc-input-row) {
		display: flex;
		justify-content: center;
	}

	:global(.pddc-input-wrap) {
		width: 100%;
		max-width: 520px;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 10px;
		align-items: stretch;
	}

	:global(.pddc-label) {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);
		letter-spacing: 0.5px;
		text-align: center;
	}

	:global(.pddc-input) {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.3);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 16px 24px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #ffffff;
		text-align: center;
		outline: none;
		cursor: pointer;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease, box-shadow 0.2s ease;
	}

	:global(.pddc-input:focus) {
		border-color: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.8);
		box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.15);
	}

	:global(.pddc-note) {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 13px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.6;
		margin: 0;
		text-align: center;
		background: rgba(236, 72, 153, 0.06);
		border: 1px solid rgba(236, 72, 153, 0.18);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 12px 14px;
	}

	:global(.pddc-results) {
		margin-top: 14px;
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.2);
		border-radius: 20px;
		padding: 28px 24px;
		box-shadow: 0 0 50px rgba(236, 72, 153, 0.06);
	}

	:global(.pddc-main) {
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: 18px;
	}

	:global(.pddc-main-kicker) {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: 2px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.45);
		margin-bottom: 10px;
	}

	:global(.pddc-main-date) {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 44px;
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -2px;
		line-height: 1.05;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
		margin-bottom: 10px;
	}

	:global(.pddc-main-sub) {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);
		line-height: 1.6;
		margin: 0;
	}

	:global(.pddc-main-sub strong) {
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.85);
		font-weight: 600;
	}

	:global(.pddc-stats) {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
		gap: 12px;
		margin-bottom: 18px;
	}

	:global(.pddc-stat) {
		background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.06);
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.18);
		border-radius: 14px;
		padding: 16px 14px;
		text-align: center;
	}

	:global(.pddc-stat-num) {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 18px;
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -0.5px;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
		margin-bottom: 6px;
	}

	:global(.pddc-stat-label) {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 11px;
		font-weight: 600;
		letter-spacing: 1px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.35);
	}

	:global(.pddc-progress) {
		margin-bottom: 14px;
	}

	:global(.pddc-progress-top) {
		display: flex;
		justify-content: space-between;
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
		margin-bottom: 8px;
	}

	:global(.pddc-progress-track) {
		height: 10px;
		background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
		border-radius: 999px;
		overflow: hidden;
	}

	:global(.pddc-progress-fill) {
		height: 100%;
		width: 0%;
		background: linear-gradient(90deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		border-radius: 999px;
		transition: width 0.4s ease;
	}

	:global(.pddc-disclaimer) {
		background: rgba(236, 72, 153, 0.05);
		border-left: 3px solid #ec4899;
		border-radius: 0 12px 12px 0;
		padding: 14px 18px;
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);
		line-height: 1.6;
	}

	.pdd-section-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.pdd-how {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.pdd-how-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		padding: 24px;
	}

	.pdd-how-card p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0 0 16px;
	}

	.pdd-how-card p:last-child {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}

	.pdd-faq {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.pdd-faq-list {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 8px;
	}

	.pdd-faq-item {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		overflow: hidden;
	}

	.pdd-faq-question {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		font-weight: 600;
		padding: 18px 24px;
		cursor: pointer;
		list-style: none;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.pdd-faq-question::-webkit-details-marker {
		display: none;
	}

	.pdd-faq-question::after {
		content: '+';
		float: right;
		font-size: 18px;
		font-weight: 700;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.pdd-faq-item[open] .pdd-faq-question::after {
		content: '−';
	}

	.pdd-faq-answer {
		padding: 0 24px 18px;
	}

	.pdd-faq-answer p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.pdd-related {
		border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		padding-top: 40px;
	}

	.pdd-related-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.pdd-related-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		gap: 12px;
	}

	.pdd-related-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 20px 16px;
		text-align: center;
		text-decoration: none;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
	}

	.pdd-related-card:hover {
		border-color: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.4);
	}

	.pdd-related-name {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	@media (max-width: 600px) {
		.pdd-title {
			font-size: 44px;
			letter-spacing: -2px;
		}

		:global(.pddc-main-date) {
			font-size: 34px;
		}

		:global(.pddc-stats) {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}

		.pdd-related-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
	}
</style>

